Source: RFE/RL, "Trump Announces 3-Day Cease-Fire In Russia-Ukraine War; Zelenskyy Vows No Red Square Attacks." By RFE/RL, May 08, 2026 08:39 CET, updated 20:55 CET. The article states that US President Donald Trump announced a three-day cease-fire in the war between Russia and Ukraine, with both sides quickly confirming they had agreed to the truce along with a major prisoner swap. It reports Trump's May 8 Truth Social post announcing a "THREE DAY CEASEFIRE (May 9th, 10th, and 11th) in the War between Russia and Ukraine." The article states Trump added that the truce would include "suspension of all Kinetic activity" and a swap of 1,000 prisoners from each side. It reports that Zelenskyy, in a Telegram post, confirmed he had agreed to a prisoner swap and said the three-day "cease-fire regime must also be established," and that he ordered his military not to attack Red Square during the May 9 Victory Day military parade. It also states that Putin aide Yury Ushakov followed with a statement saying Russia had agreed to the three-day cease-fire and the exchange of prisoners. Adverse/context language: the article says it earlier appeared that a Kremlin-proposed Victory Day cease-fire had collapsed within hours, with Ukraine and Russia reporting hundreds of violations a day before the parade; it also reports drone/artillery/missile strikes and retaliatory-strike claims around the period.